review_blob: Poured rom a 750ml bottle into a trappist glass, the color is a ruby brown with nice head, the aroma is a sweet molasses, candied fruit, sweet taste upfront with some candied fruit, licorice but the alcohol is prominent with a lasting warmth after the sip.

review_blob: Poured from a bottle into a snifter, the color is a reddish brown with thin almost nonexistent head the aroma is sweet malt, dried fruit and some citrus, taste of caramel, sweetness of dried fruit, some licorice, vanilla, lingering bitterness and a long lasting warmth going down.

Pleasant surprise. Not what I expected but still enjoyed, dark brown in color with a thin head, crisp carbonation, thin mouth feel, taste of malt, some fruitness, sourness is prevalent, the lingering sourness and then more warmth than you would expect from a 7.2 abv. Try it with an open mind dont expect a Brown and you may like it. I did.
